<div class="container mt-5">
  <h1 class="text-center mb-4">About</h1>
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
      <p class="text-justify lead">
        This website allows you to search for people's favorite dish from one of the Country's National Dishes! You can navigate and check individual information and search things up.
      </p>
      <h2 class="text-center my-4">Data sources</h2>
      <div class="mb-3">
        <h3 class="h4 mb-2">REST Countries</h3>
        <p class="text-justify">
          This API is a RESTful service that provides information about countries' population, region, geo-location, and more. This API is what I used to fill the Country Table. For references: <a href="https://restcountries.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://restcountries.com/</a>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mb-3">
        <h3 class="h4 mb-2">Faker</h3>
        <p class="text-justify">
          I am using a library called Faker, purposefully used to generate fake data. I filled my Users Table using data generated by Faker. For references: <a href="https://github.com/faker-ruby/faker" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://github.com/faker-ruby/faker</a>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="mb-4">
        <h3 class="h4 mb-2">National Dishes</h3>
        <p class="text-justify">
          A small-scale API that provides the national dishes of countries. This API is used to fill the Dish table. For references: <a href="https://github.com/drmonkeyninja/country.json/blob/master/src/country-by-national-dish.json" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">https://github.com/drmonkeyninja/country.json/blob/master/src/country-by-national-dish.json</a>
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="text-center">
        <%= image_tag 'Intro-rails-erd', alt: 'Global Image', class:'img-fluid mb-4' %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
